WEBVTT

00:06.297 --> 00:08.129
Cyd, in honor
of the one-month
anniversary

00:08.129 --> 00:09.630
of you coming
to live with us,

00:09.630 --> 00:11.512
I've prepared
a special dish.

00:11.512 --> 00:14.975
Good, 'cause I've got
just the hole in my face
to stuff it into.

00:16.807 --> 00:20.061
Cyd, are you eating
before Mom tells
the story of the meal?

00:20.731 --> 00:21.982
No.

00:23.444 --> 00:24.445
Maybe.

00:27.358 --> 00:29.820
No.

00:29.820 --> 00:32.493
Kids, tonight's dinner
is a free-trade casserole

00:32.493 --> 00:34.325
with sustainable
mixed-veggies

00:34.325 --> 00:36.957
and cruelty-free chicken.

00:36.957 --> 00:39.250
How can chicken
be cruelty-free?

00:39.250 --> 00:40.541
It's not still alive, is it?

00:40.541 --> 00:42.253
Well, no. But it
was cruelty-free

00:42.253 --> 00:43.424
right until the end,

00:43.424 --> 00:44.375
where they probably
had to use

00:44.375 --> 00:45.666
a tiny-little
bit of cruelty.

00:45.666 --> 00:47.378
Just enough to...

00:47.378 --> 00:49.170
The skin is
really crispy!

00:50.551 --> 00:51.592
Like Chet at
the water park.

00:51.592 --> 00:53.974
(ALL LAUGHING)

00:53.974 --> 00:56.097
Oh, I get it.
He got sunburned
at the water park.

00:56.097 --> 00:58.639
No, he really likes
the crispy chicken there.

00:58.639 --> 01:00.020
We don't joke
about sunburn.

01:00.020 --> 01:01.352
With our
family's complexion,

01:01.352 --> 01:04.024
we all fry up like
center-cut bacon.

01:04.024 --> 01:06.527
Oh, I had no idea.
Sorry, Chet.

01:06.527 --> 01:09.570
I'm Bret.
You can tell because
I have more freckles.

01:09.570 --> 01:11.362
And he's
the ladies' man.

01:12.072 --> 01:13.244
'Sup?

01:14.405 --> 01:15.696
Well, everybody dig in.

01:17.698 --> 01:19.540
This is delicious, Astrid.

01:19.540 --> 01:21.872
Even before my parents left
for their archeological dig,

01:21.872 --> 01:24.255
they were never
really around much
for family dinners.

01:24.255 --> 01:25.756
Well, we are,
and we want
you to feel

01:25.756 --> 01:27.378
like this
is your home.

01:27.378 --> 01:29.170
Then set me in front
of the television

01:29.170 --> 01:32.012
with a leftover beef rib
and go do your thing.

01:32.593 --> 01:34.305
Ha-ha-ha.

01:34.305 --> 01:36.477
Would you laugh if I said
the rib was crispy?

01:36.477 --> 01:39.350
Oh no, sweetheart.
That means you're not
cooking them properly.

01:41.642 --> 01:43.063
I'm home.

01:43.063 --> 01:44.645
Hi, Dad.
 Hey, Dad!
How was work?

01:44.645 --> 01:46.647
Oh, just another
soul-crushing day

01:46.647 --> 01:49.940
trapped in the toothless
maw of corporate America.

01:49.940 --> 01:51.111
How was your day,
sweetie?

01:52.613 --> 01:54.114
Dad, you're
such a kidder.

01:54.114 --> 01:55.326
Sure, let's go with that.

01:56.657 --> 01:58.789
Mr. Marcus, what
exactly do you do?

01:58.789 --> 02:00.371
I've never really
been sure.

02:00.371 --> 02:02.413
Well, a lot of people think
that accounting is boring

02:02.413 --> 02:04.505
but what they
don't realize,

02:04.505 --> 02:06.377
there's a lot
of math involved.

02:08.048 --> 02:10.511
Cyd, for your one
month-aversary...

02:10.511 --> 02:11.882
We made you a cake!

02:11.882 --> 02:14.305
Let's go finish
decorating it, Bret!

02:14.305 --> 02:15.636
To the bedroom, Chet!

02:17.308 --> 02:18.969
They're decorating
a cake in their bedroom?

02:18.969 --> 02:20.931
Our boys are
free spirits, Norm.

02:20.931 --> 02:22.603
Don't stifle
their creativity.

02:22.603 --> 02:24.104
Is it really creativity,

02:24.104 --> 02:26.146
or is it not knowing what
different rooms are for?

02:26.146 --> 02:28.609
They moved their beds
into my mancave.

02:28.609 --> 02:30.191
That's their bedroom.

02:30.191 --> 02:31.402
Used to be my mancave.

02:33.324 --> 02:35.196
CHET: Don't let go
of the cart, Bret!

02:35.196 --> 02:37.448
BRET: No, you don't let
go of the cart, Chet!

02:37.448 --> 02:38.869
(THUDDING)

02:43.624 --> 02:45.376
Is it bad that
I'm still gonna
eat that?

02:47.838 --> 02:50.551
♪ I know it sounds crazy

02:50.551 --> 02:53.464
♪ But time doesn't faze me

02:53.464 --> 02:57.348
♪ Ever since it lost
 its hold on me

02:57.348 --> 02:59.179
♪ Hey, hey

02:59.179 --> 03:01.802
♪ Hung out till midnight

03:01.802 --> 03:04.565
♪ Missed the curfew,
 that's all right

03:04.565 --> 03:08.188
♪ I'm back to bed
 and right on time,
 you'll see

03:09.900 --> 03:11.232
♪ Whenever

03:11.232 --> 03:12.613
♪ You need me

03:12.613 --> 03:15.316
♪ I'm right there with you

03:15.316 --> 03:16.657
♪ Whenever

03:16.657 --> 03:18.078
♪ There's something

03:18.078 --> 03:20.951
♪ You wanna redo

03:20.951 --> 03:23.744
♪ The clock is ticking
 but not for me

03:23.744 --> 03:26.377
♪ I'm living in
 a different reality

03:26.377 --> 03:27.628
♪ Whenever

03:27.628 --> 03:29.089
♪ Whatever

03:29.089 --> 03:30.541
♪ Wherever

03:30.541 --> 03:33.674
♪ I'm right there with you

03:33.674 --> 03:35.796
♪ I'm right there with you

03:35.796 --> 03:36.797
♪ Hey, hey ♪

